  "title": "M&E Quantity Surveyor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Benefits</strong></p><p>•        0–20% Monthly Performance Related Pay</p><p>•        2% Monthly Medical Allowance</p><p>•        Yearly Salary Increment</p><p></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p>•        Review and interpret Mechanical and/or Electrical tender documents and drawings.</p><p>•        Prepare quantity take-offs, bills of quantities (BQ), and cost estimates for M&E works.</p><p>•        Support preliminary Mechanical or Electrical design for Design & Build tenders.</p><p>•        Prepare technical documentation and proposals for tender submissions.</p><p>•        Manage contract administration for main contractors and subcontractors.</p><p>•        Review Letters of Award from clients or main contractors.</p><p>•        Source, evaluate, negotiate, and shortlist suppliers and subcontractors based on project requirements.</p><p>•        Prepare monthly progress claims and process subcontractor and supplier payments.</p><p>•        Monitor project budgets, propose value engineering solutions, and coordinate closely with site teams.</p><p></p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p>•        Diploma or Degree in Quantity Surveying, Mechanical Engineering, Electrical Engineering, or related disciplines.</p><p>•        Minimum 2 years of relevant working experience.</p><p>•        Experience in either Mechanical OR Electrical works is acceptable.</p><p>•        Experience in cost control, tendering, or contract administration will be an advantage.</p><p>•        Able to work independently and collaboratively in a team environment.</p><p>•        Good communication and interpersonal skills.</p><p>•        Able to manage multiple tasks and meet project deadlines in a fast-paced environment.<br /></p><p></p><p>Maxhunt Resource Pte Ltd | EA Licence: 22C1322<br />\nCynthia Lai | Registration No: R25146301</p>",
